edu.ucla.sspace.common

Class StaticSemanticSpace

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ucla.sspace.common.StaticSemanticSpace
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SemanticSpace

    public class StaticSemanticSpace
extends Object
implements SemanticSpace
    An unmodifiable SemanticSpace whose data is loaded into memory from an .sspace file. Instance of this class perform no document processing, and the processDocument and processSpace methods throw an UnsupportedOperationException.

    In general, users should call SemanticSpaceUtils.loadSemanticSpace(File) rather than create an instance of this class directly.

    This class is thread-safe

    See Also:
    OnDiskSemanticSpace, SemanticSpaceUtils, SemanticSpaceUtils.SSpaceFormat
